# Execution Policy

## Trigger

When the user says “делай следующую задачу”, run the backlog-driven execution loop.

## Context budget

Read small indexes first. Avoid archives by default.

## Task selection

Select a task that is:

- `ready`;
- in the active milestone;
- not blocked;
- dependencies done;
- highest priority;
- risk acceptable without extra approval.

## High-risk approval

Ask the user before delegating high-risk tasks.

## Status transitions

```text
ready -> in_progress -> review -> done
review -> ready   if changes requested
any -> blocked    if a decision/dependency is missing
```

## Done criteria

A task is done only after:

- acceptance criteria met;
- validation evidence exists;
- Opus decision is ACCEPT;
- task file moved to done;
- index/state/log updated.


## Orchestrator modes

Primary mode:

- Opus may execute normal backlog-driven flow and make architecture/review decisions within policy.

Conservative fallback mode:

- ChatGPT may continue low/medium-risk ready tasks.
- ChatGPT must not approve high-risk work without explicit user approval.
- ChatGPT must not change roadmap, strategy, architecture, or validation policy without user approval.

Emergency Codex-only mode:

- allowed only for trivial scoped tasks.
- not allowed for high-risk or strategic work.

Switching modes requires updating `docs/ai/orchestrator/handoff-state.md`.
